!1| Vim !1|

!2| Done !2|

- Shortcut that changes the current working directory to the directory in where the file persists.
- Like ranger file moving. Map "l" to open a folder or a file.
- Kebinding that open the folder that contains my templates.
- Highlight separators considering hierarchy.

!3| Unnecessary !3|

- Keybinding that changes the current working directory to a the directory which contain the file from the current buffer, open NERDTree, make the current working directory be the same as it was before.
	EXPLANATION
	It is more convenient to open NERDTree in the directory where the file from the current buffer is, this way it is not necessary to change the current working directory. Note that this is what I wanted to accomplish in the first place.

