!3| NERDTree !3|

- Appending files to current buffer using the NERDTree menu.
	When I press a key while the cursor is on a file from the NERDTree menu, vim reads that file into the buffer where the cursor was, before NERDTree was opened.
	
	You should consider that NERDTree knows which window toggled the NERDTree menu, because when you open a file using the NERDTree menu, it knows in which windows.

- Yank file to a given register from the NERDTree menu just by pressing: y<register>".

